

Server:

The server should recognize the resource being asked for and handle it appropriately
The server should be able to read tag data from mp3s in the served directory
The server should be able to convert tag data to an XML representation and return it in the HTTP response

The server should accept POST data and update mp3 tags appropriately based on the XML data in the request body

The server should be able to query the musicbrainz API to search tag data




Client:

The client should take command line arguments and create the proper HTTP request
The client should print information based on it's success or failure
The client and server should have a consistent way of handling errors through the HTTP responses


